If SWAP was set up with 16B and you received an error message:

Please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu including the following information: 

  • Subject: EECS 16B Swap Message
  • Please let me know if you received a message that you were not enrolled due to the swap set
  • Your SID
  • The class you set the swap with (MUST INCLUDE: Course & Course # and the Class CNN)

If you received a time conflict message please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu to inform me.

I have a swap in progress for a class that I'm currently enrolled in, trying to get into 16b instead (they're both at the same time).

Today I got an email saying that I was not enrolled in 16b because of a time conflict, which I assume is the class that the swap is for.

When I get into 16b that class should be dropped automatically, so how should I move forward with this time conflict message? I really would like to be enrolled in 16b for the fall!
